          <!-- VMware -->
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker current"></div>
            <details class="timeline-content" open>
              <summary class="timeline-header">
                <div class="flex-1">
                  <h3 class="font-bold text-[var(--color-heading)]">VMware</h3>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-accent)]">Customer Success Architect</p>
                </div>
                <span class="timeline-date">2019 - Present</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="timeline-body">
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>Customer Success Architect - Success 360</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">September 2020 - Present</span>
                  <p>My role entails close collaboration with customers who have purchased Success 360. I provide architectural guidance for customers developing highly automated, secure, available, resilient, and multi-cloud architectural designs. The designs typically need to seamlessly integrate with very complex estates which requires focussed problem-solving and analytical skills.</p>
                  <p>In addition to architectural design, I also formulate architectural roadmaps that harmonise with both customer and product roadmaps. My alignment to customers are long-term which enables intimate understanding of their requirements and time to develop highly trusted relationships.</p>
                  <p class="achievement">üèÜ 'Raising the Bar' award by Customer Success team for FY21</p>
                  <p class="achievement">üèÜ 'Execution' award from Professional Services for FY23 Q1</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>Chief Technology Office (OCTO) Ambassador</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">February 2021 - Present</span>
                  <p>In my role as a OCTO Ambassador, I have the honour of acting as a conduit between our customers and our research and development teams. This can be with regards to awareness and enablement of new innovation through to full design partnerships. I place a particular focus on innovation on edge, IT/OT convergence, sustainability and carbon reduction.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>Embedded Architect - Advanced Customer Engagement</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">July 2019 - September 2020</span>
                  <p>During this role, I worked as an embedded architect within strategic alliance partner's hybrid cloud architecture and engineering teams. My primary responsibility was to be on-point for all architectural aspects of the full VMware product portfolio.</p>
                  <p>Delivering architectural consultancy, technical enablement, design partnerships, feature requests, large deal support, executive briefings, developed cohesive technical roadmaps, automation, infrastructure as code, continuous integration, and operational hygiene programs.</p>
                  <p class="achievement">üèÜ Annual Advanced Customer Engagement 'Leadership' award for FY20</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>

          <!-- DXC Technology -->
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <details class="timeline-content">
              <summary class="timeline-header">
                <div class="flex-1">
                  <h3 class="font-bold text-[var(--color-heading)]">DXC Technology</h3>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-accent)]">Principal Architect</p>
                </div>
                <span class="timeline-date">2016 - 2019</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="timeline-body">
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>Managed Services for VMware Private Cloud</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">May 2017 - July 2019</span>
                  <p>In my role as the leader of the design and engineering team, I was tasked with developing a standardised Infrastructure as a Service private cloud offering that boasted a comprehensive self-service Platform as a Service (PaaS) catalogue.</p>
                  <p>The PaaS service catalogue offered self-service delivery of servers, database engines, middleware, security services, backup, disaster recovery, firewall, and network function virtualisation.</p>
                  <p>The resulting solution proved to be a success, with customers across industries such as defence, government secure, financial, and healthcare adopting it. The self-service portal-driven automation and orchestration workflows encompassed provisioning, guest customisation, day two lifecycle management, and billing.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>Managed Mid-range on VMware</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">May 2017 - July 2019</span>
                  <p>As the technical design and engineering lead for the global Managed Mid-range offering, I spearheaded the development of a highly standardised hosting platform that enabled streamlined day two operational support. Unlike the Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) offering, this solution offered a more personalised approach to workload deployment, with greater flexibility for customisation.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>Modern Platform Initiative</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">December 2016 - July 2019</span>
                  <p>In my role as technical lead, I led an initiative to streamline the delivery of a VMware-based virtual hosting platform by industrialising the process. To achieve this, I created a modular technical design and configuration that could be consistently built by technology partners such as Dell, Hitachi, and HPE in their build factories.</p>
                  <p>I also established a delivery workflow process that integrated with all data centre systems, from factory delivery through all the on-site systems integrations.</p>
                  <p>The benefits of industrialising the delivery of the VMware virtual hosting platform were significant for the business, including enhanced sales capabilities, accurate pricing of deals, consistent global delivery, and reduced delivery timelines.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
