                  <h4>BizCloud Hyper-Converged</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">March 2014 - December 2015</span>
                  <p>As part of a team, I helped design, build, and automate a dedicated private cloud infrastructure using hyper-converged technology for VMware's SDDC. This cloud offering was made available for Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS) through the Service Mesh Agility Platform.</p>
                  <p>Additionally, I developed a capability demonstration which showcased the consumption of IaaS using a Continuous Integration/Continuous Deployment (CI/CD) pipeline based on Jenkins. This pipeline was responsible for delivering various components such as servers, applications, Software-Defined Networking (SDN), Distributed Firewall (DFW), and Network Function Virtualisation (NFV).</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>UK&I Healthcare - DevOps Transformation</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">April 2013 - March 2014</span>
                  <p>As a systems engineer and leader within a DevOps team, I oversaw the transformation of our development workflow from a static release process to a continuous delivery approach. This was achieved through the use of Service Mesh Agility Platform to orchestrate the provisioning of virtual servers and the handoff to Puppet for applying the desired configuration state all the way to running the application.</p>
                  <p>By adopting declarative infrastructure as code (IaC), we were able to improve the availability of our applications while also reducing operational support costs. The implementation of a continuous integration and continuous delivery (CI/CD) pipeline brought numerous benefits across the development and production lifecycle, fostering closer collaboration between IT Operations, testing, and Development teams.</p>
                  <p class="achievement">üèÜ CSC Global Award for Technical Excellence 2015</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>UK&I Healthcare - Storage Consolidation</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">December 2012 - April 2013</span>
                  <p>As a member of a team responsible for evaluating potential replacement storage subsystems for a multi-petabyte migration zero data loss storage platform with a requirement of 99.99% availability, I contributed to the assessment of both EMC VMAX and Hitachi VSP systems.</p>
                  <p>Following the selection of the chosen storage sub-system, I took on a leadership role in the platform systems engineering and implementation of a SAN consolidation effort. This initiative involved migrating from assorted legacy Hitachi SAN systems to a unified pair of Hitachi Virtual Storage Platform SAN, resulting in increased efficiency and a streamlined storage infrastructure.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>CSC Internal - Global Systems Management</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">January 2012 - November 2012</span>
                  <p>As the lead for technical design, engineering, and delivery, I oversaw the creation of a vSphere hosting platform dedicated to hosting global systems management tooling.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>UK&I Healthcare (Chennai) - Stateless Application Deployment</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">August 2011 - December 2011</span>
                  <p>As the engineering and delivery lead, I spearheaded the development and implementation of an application deployment and upgrade solution designed to render application and web servers stateless. This was achieved by leveraging virtual hard drive detachment and attachment, as well as updates to application configuration files. To automate the process, we utilised PowerShell scripting to orchestrate NetApp SAN snapshots, VMware VM hardware changes, and in-guest Windows changes.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>UK&I Healthcare - vCloud Director IaaS</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">October 2011</span>
                  <p>In my role as the technical design, engineering, and delivery lead, I oversaw the creation and implementation of a vCloud Director self-service Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS) private cloud, which was based on VCE vBlock hardware. This private cloud was deployed within a hospital trust setting.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>CSC Internal (Copenhagen) - Nordics vCloud Director</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">April 2011 - August 2011</span>
                  <p>I played a key role in the design of a vCloud Director self-service Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS) private cloud intended for internal use in the Nordics region. Following the design phase, I assumed the position of technical lead and was responsible for overseeing the implementation of the solution, collaborating closely with local delivery engineers throughout the process.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>UK&I Healthcare (Chennai) - VMware Hosting Redesign</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">August 2009 - December 2011</span>
                  <p>I led the redesign, engineering, and delivery of a VMware-based virtual hosting solution, which was designed to scale in order to meet growing demand and provide site DR business continuity capability. Through a partnership with NetApp, we were able to deliver an innovative solution.</p>
                  <p class="achievement">üèÜ NetApp EMEA Innovation Award 2011</p>
                  <p class="achievement">üèÜ CSC Global Presidents Award for Excellence 2011</p>
                </div>
