                <div class="role">
                  <h4>UK Border Agency (Belgrade)</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">June 2007</span>
                  <p>I played a role in the delivery of an IT biometric identity solution for a new Visa Application Center. Although it was a small project, it was highly visible, and I had the opportunity to meet the UK ambassador to Serbia during its implementation.</p>
                  <p class="achievement">üèÜ MCA International Award 2007 (as part of broader multi-site effort)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                  <h4>UK&I Healthcare - Enterprise Automation</h4>
                  <span class="role-date">September 2004 - June 2008</span>
                  <p>My focus was on automating the end-to-end delivery process for customer applications running on 4,500 physical servers, operating in a complex network environment with strict firewalls, and spread across multiple data centers with petabytes of synchronously replicated data.</p>
                  <p>The solution involved the creation of reusable, modular scripting assets that were stored in Altiris, with unique server identities delivered by passing variables to the scripts and orchestrating the correct components in the correct order.</p>
                  <p>This deployment was Veritas's largest worldwide deployment of VCS for Windows and VCS for VMware at the time.</p>
                  <p class="achievement">üèÜ CSC EMEA Presidents Award for Technical Excellence 2005</p>
